02/11/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Italy on Friday (October 31st) officially asked Tirana to extradite 128 Albanians sentenced in Rome. 
Alfredo Mantovani, deputy secretary of Italy's interior ministry, requested the move during his visit in Tirana, which included meetings with justice and interior ministry officials and prosecutors. 
Mantovani noted international arrest warrants have been issued for the criminals, who are believed to be hiding in Albania. 
(Makfax, Alsat M, Koha Jone - 01/11/08)
